      <p class="section-label">Section 03 — Scaling</p>
      <h2 class="cs-heading" style="max-width: 720px;">From sole contributor to system steward</h2>

      <div class="cs-prose" style="margin-top: 40px; max-width: 800px;">
        <p>With expansion came a fundamentally different challenge. Seven designers joined the team. The platform roadmap grew to include a visual drag-and-drop agent builder, MCP server integrations, automated testing and evaluation, analytics, and versioning — all due within eight months.</p>
        <p>My role shifted from builder to multiplier. I structured design ownership across parallel workstreams, established shared interaction patterns to prevent fragmentation, led design reviews, and kept the system coherent under pressure. At the same time, I stayed in the work — taking direct IC ownership of the highest-leverage areas while making sure the team had clarity and support to move fast.</p>
        <p>I also produced executive-facing demos used in board presentations, partnered with sales on customer-facing narratives, and ran customer interviews that shaped prioritization. Keeping stakeholders aligned under a compressed timeline was as much a design challenge as anything on screen.</p>
