      <h2 class="cs-statement">Autonomy is only safe when it's transparent.</h2>

      <div class="cs-two-col">
        <div class="cs-prose">
          <p>A consistent thread across both phases was this: as systems become more capable, the designer's job is to preserve human agency — not just enable automation. Every decision about escalation logic, override states, and transparency patterns was made with that in mind.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-prose">
          <p>I apply the same principle internally. Teams move faster when trust is high. I lead through clarity, direct communication, and staying close to the work — not above it.</p>
        </div>
